Let's simplify this expression and see where we end up.

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{\left(\dfrac{3x}{2}\right)}{\left(\dfrac{3}{x}+2\right)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{\left(\dfrac{3x}{2}\right)}{\left(\dfrac{3}{x}+{\dfrac{2x}{x}}\right)} ~~~~~~~~\text{because }2 = 2 \cdot \dfrac{x}{x} = \dfrac{2x}{x}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{\left(\dfrac{3x}{2}\right)}{\left(\dfrac{3+{2x}}{{x}}\right)}
\end{align}$

$\begin{align}
&=\dfrac{3x}{2}\div\dfrac{3+2x}{x}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{3x}{2} \cdot \dfrac{x}{3+2x} ~~~~~~~~ \text{Multiply by the reciprocal.}
\end{align}$

$\begin{align}
&=\dfrac{3x^2}{2(3+2x)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{3x^2}{6+4x}
\end{align}$

Next, we can use fraction multiplication to write the expression as a single fraction. 

$\begin{align}\dfrac{a-5}{5a}\times\dfrac{a}{a-5}&=\dfrac{a(a-5)}{5a(a-5)}
\end{align}$

The numerator and denominator share a common factor of $x(x+1)$.

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{x(3x+3)}{x(4x+4)} &= \dfrac{3x(x+1)}{4x(x+1)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac34
\end{align}$
